  "name": "Nagaraja COU1 — Non-cannulated pedicle screw compression-bending credibility assessment (Adversarial W-AR-05)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for FEA prediction of ASTM F1717 static compression-bending performance of a non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct. COU1 is the validation activity itself — the FEA model ensemble (FDA, Ansys, DePuy Synthes) is compared against N=11 experimental constructs across two laboratories. All 13 V&V 40 factors assessed; one factor (Test conditions) below required level due to single test condition. This package contains synthetic adversarial content targeting W-AR-05: a validation result whose comparator dataset is present in narrative but whose comparedAgainst link is absent, and a second validation result whose comparator originates from a cannulated-screw test series — overlapping on all geometry and loading parameters except the cannulation channel, which alters torsional and bending stiffness distributions in a manner material to the declared QoIs.",
