      "name": "Primary QoI comparison — stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement",
      "description": "FEA ensemble predictions for construct stiffness (N/mm), yield force (N), and force at 40 mm displacement (N) were evaluated against the experimental dataset collected under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending conditions. Across N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm constructs, all three QoIs fell within the pre-specified 10% tolerance band. The normalised error metric E/uval was below 1.96 for each QoI, confirming adequate predictive accuracy. The experimental reference series used for this comparison is well-characterised, with full traceability to laboratory notebooks and calibrated load-cell records. Agreement between the two participating laboratories (FDA CDRH and DePuy Synthes) was within 3.1% for stiffness and 4.7% for yield force, supporting confidence in the experimental ground truth. No systematic bias was identified in the residuals. This result is considered the primary evidence of model adequacy for the declared COU."
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/comparator-mismatch-cannulated-ref",
