      "name": "Cross-design sensitivity check — comparison against cannulated-screw experimental series",
      "description": "As a supplementary validation exercise, the same FEA ensemble was evaluated against an independent experimental dataset obtained from the companion cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw construct tested under identical ASTM F1717 static compression-bending protocol (same rod diameter, same vertebral body surrogate, same actuator displacement rate, same laboratory personnel and equipment). The cannulated series comprises N=11 constructs and was collected concurrently with the non-cannulated series, providing near-identical test conditions. FEA predictions for construct stiffness and yield force agreed with the cannulated experimental data to within 8.3% and 7.6% respectively, both within the 10% acceptance criterion. The modelling team notes that the cannulated geometry introduces a 3.2 mm central bore, which is absent in the COU design; however, the bore is considered a minor geometric perturbation that does not materially alter the global compression-bending response at the construct level. The strong agreement observed across both design variants is interpreted as evidence of the framework's generalisability and further supports acceptance of the primary non-cannulated validation result.",
